    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-06T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-06T21:00:00-05:00" n="195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.24/271: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-06T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 6, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5581. Department’s 5534, November 5. Following telegram has been received from
                    Tehran:</p>
                <p>[Here follow first two paragraphs of telegram No. 359, November 4, 6 p.m., from
                    the Minister in Iran, printed on <ref target="#pg_176">page 176</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Please convey substance of above to Foreign Office and state that Department
                    hopes action on wheat declaration and announcement regarding shipment 25,000
                    tons wheat may be taken immediately. Please advise us urgently of British
                    decision.</p>
                <p>For your information and comments there is quoted below Section 2 of Tehran
                    telegram under reference:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of last paragraph of telegram No. 359.]</p>
                <p>Additional demands and suggestions mentioned included removal of currency control
                    from Majlis and establishment of four-power currency board.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
